"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437224","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-12-18","<p>The government was elected with a mandate to reform the UK’s human rights framework. We are considering the implications of a Bill of Rights on devolution as we develop our proposals. We will, of course, fully engage with the devolved administrations.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"2015-12-18T12:55:02.357Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437224/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437224/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437224/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-12-10","Bill of Rights: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, whether he plans for the proposed British Bill of Rights to apply to Scotland.","false","Biography information for Richard Arkless","Dumfries and Galloway","Richard  Arkless","19673"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437225","Department of Health","false","2015-12-15","<p>Public Health England provides local information for performance monitoring in the restricted access section of the National Drug Treatment Monitoring System website, but does not publish national data centrally.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison","19625","2015-12-15T15:04:59.237Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437225/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437225/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437225/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-12-10","Prisons: Health Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many prisoners received treatment for (a) alcohol addiction, (b) drug addiction and (c) any other addiction in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Andy Slaughter","Hammersmith","Andy Slaughter","19690"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437226","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-12-17","<p>The vast majority of NOMS staff undertake their duties with honesty and integrity. However, like all large organisations a minority of staff engage in corrupt activity. This is particularly challenging for NOMS given its role. We are committed to ensure that corruption will be investigated and eliminated to ensure prisons remain a safe and secure environment for staff, prisoners and visitors. Allegations against staff that are potentially criminal in nature are referred to the police for investigation.</p><br /><p>A Corruption Prevention Unit delivers the key elements of the Agency’s corruption prevention strategy, including: detection, enforcement, training and support for staff. As part of this work NOMS collates records centrally of staff dismissed for offences which meet its definition of corruption.</p><br /><p>The number of dismissals over the last five years of NOMS staff for corruption related offences has been provided in the table below.</p><br /><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Dismissals</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010</p></td><td><p>16</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011</p></td><td><p>17</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p>14</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>16</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014</p></td><td><p>16</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Total</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>79</strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table><br /><p>Notes:</p><ol><li>Data covers staff directly employed by NOMS and not contractor staff.</li><li>The information provided has been drawn from live administrative data systems which may be amended at any time. Although care is taken when processing and analysing the returns, the detail collected is subject to the inaccuracies inherent in any large scale recording system.</li></ol>","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous",,"2015-12-17T10:51:32.957Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437226/answer","Biography information for Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437226/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437226/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-12-10","National Offender Management Service: Corruption","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many NOMS staff have been dismissed for corruption in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Mary Glindon","North Tyneside","Mary Glindon","19593"
