"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436835","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-12-15","<p>There are no current plans to change the ownership of HMP Manchester.</p>","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous",,"2015-12-15T12:44:15.737Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436835/answer","Biography information for Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436835/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436835/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-12-09","Manchester Prison: Ownership","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what his plans are for the future ownership of HM Prison Manchester; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Graham Stringer","Blackley and Broughton","Graham Stringer","19498"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436836","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-12-17","<p>Since November 2008 (when the Forced Marriage (Civil Protection) Act 2007 came into force) there have been 118 Force Marriage Protection Orders issued in total in West Yorkshire.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2015-12-17T10:55:34.143Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436836/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436836/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436836/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-12-09","Forced Marriage: West Yorkshire","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many forced marriage prevention orders have been issued in West Yorkshire since the Forced Marriage (Civil Protection) Act 2007 came into force.","false","Biography information for Mary Creagh","Wakefield","Mary Creagh","19494"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436837","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-12-17","<p>As was stated in the Answer to HL 2604, the 3.5 full time equivalent staff who worked under the Just Solutions International (JSi) brand also worked on other core business within the National offender Management Service. Exact calculations were not made to apportion staff time, salaries, expenses or bonuses on JSi.</p>","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous",,"2015-12-17T10:47:11.997Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436837/answer","Biography information for Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436837/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436837/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-12-09","Just Solutions International: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, pursuant to the Answer of 27 October 2015 to Question HL2604, what the cost to the public purse is of salary, expenses and bonuses of the 3.5 full-time staff who worked under the JSi brand.","false","Biography information for Andy Slaughter","Hammersmith","Andy Slaughter","19495"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436838","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-12-14","<p>No funding was allocated within the National Offender Management Service (NOMS) budget for the operation of Just Solutions International (JSi), and exact calculations were not made to apportion staff time on JSi. Under the business model, services provided by JSi were to be provided on a cost recovery basis.</p>","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous",,"2015-12-14T14:21:57.13Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436838/answer","Biography information for Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436838/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436838/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-12-09","National Offender Management Service: Just Solutions International","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what proportion of the National Offender Management Service budget in (a) staffing resources, (b) allocation of civil service time and (c) funding was set aside for the operation of Just Solutions International throughout its lifespan.","false","Biography information for Andy Slaughter","Hammersmith","Andy Slaughter","19452"
