"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436155","HM Treasury","false","2015-12-16","<p>This is a matter for the Financial Conduct Authority (FCA), which is operationally independent from Government.</p><br /><p>This question has been passed on to the FCA. They will reply directly to the Honourable Member by letter. A copy of the letter will be placed in the Library of the House.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","19191 ; 19193 ; 19196 ; 19197 ; 19200 ; 19201","2015-12-16T16:24:22.887Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436155/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436155/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436155/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-12-08","Financial Services: Advisory Services","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether he is satisfied that the Financial Conduct Authority's minimum professional indemnity insurance requirements for Independent Financial Advisers provide investors with adequate protection for medium and long-term investments.","false","Biography information for Kirsten Oswald","East Renfrewshire","Kirsten  Oswald","19195"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436156","HM Treasury","false","2015-12-16","<p>Treasury Ministers and officials occasionally receive representations on regulatory issues.</p><br /><p>As was the case with previous Administrations, it is not the Treasury’s practice to provide details of all such discussions.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2015-12-16T16:15:49.357Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436156/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436156/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436156/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-12-08","Financial Services: Advisory Services","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what representations he has received on the provisions in the Financial Conduct Authority handbook IPRU-INV sch13 which allows independent financial advisers and insurers to retrospectively exclude failed schemes from an IFA's professional indemnity insurance.","false","Biography information for Kirsten Oswald","East Renfrewshire","Kirsten  Oswald","19199"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436157","HM Treasury","false","2015-12-16","<p>This is a matter for the Financial Conduct Authority (FCA), which is operationally independent from Government.</p><br /><p>This question has been passed on to the FCA. They will reply directly to the Honourable Member by letter. A copy of the letter will be placed in the Library of the House.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","19191 ; 19193 ; 19195 ; 19196 ; 19197 ; 19201","2015-12-16T16:24:22.997Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436157/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436157/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436157/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-12-08","Investment Trusts","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, when he became aware that Connaught Fund investors pursuing compensation awarded by the Financial Ombudsman Service are having their professional indemnity claims rejected because the Financial Conduct Authority handbook IPRU-INV sch13 allows independent financial advisers to operate with insurer-imposed restrictions on their insurance that exclude schemes the adviser had already recommended to clients.","false","Biography information for Kirsten Oswald","East Renfrewshire","Kirsten  Oswald","19200"
